# Private strategy / discussion notes (not for public release)
private/

# super-harness self-hosts (HG-D, 2026-06-02): this repo is itself driven by
# super-harness, so its OWN top-level .harness/ is no longer blanket-ignored.
# Following the tool's own convention, the CONFIG files (verification.yaml,
# gates.yaml, policy.yaml, sensors.yaml, source-paths.yaml, conventions.md) ARE
# committed, while the volatile/derived state (events.jsonl, state.yaml, run
# artifacts) stays ignored via the `super-harness gitignore` managed block that
# `super-harness init` appends below — do not hand-edit that block.
# (The in-tree demo under examples/demo-openspec-claude/.harness/ remains
# committed too, including its seeded events.jsonl/state.yaml, so visitors see a
# realistic post-init tree.)

# OS
.DS_Store

# Editor
.vscode/
.idea/

# Node (placeholder for future)
node_modules/
*.log

# Python build artifacts
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/

# Python virtual environments — glob so leftover review/test venvs
# (`.venv-review/`, `.venv-wheel/`, etc.) are also ignored. Smoke walk v4
# caught a sdist-build crash where hatchling included a stale `.venv-review/`
# whose `bin/python3.X` was an absolute symlink — Python 3.12+ tarfile
# refuses to extract absolute-link members. Defense in depth: the hatchling
# exclude block in `pyproject.toml [tool.hatch.build]` also excludes
# `.venv*/` so even if a venv is in-tree but un-gitignored, the sdist
# stays clean.
.venv*/

# Python caches
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# >>> super-harness gitignore (do not edit between markers)
.harness/state.yaml
.harness/events.jsonl
.harness/sensor-results/
.harness/verification-results/
.harness/operation-logs/
.harness/pending-reviews/
.harness/gate-disabled
.harness/daemon.pid
.harness/daemon.log
.harness/.*.lock
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/*.super-harness-backup.*
.codex/hooks.json
.codex/*.super-harness-backup.*
# <<< super-harness gitignore
